The paper proposes a new method for link prediction in directed graphs using graph autoencoders and variational autoencoders. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the primary focus of the paper. The paper also involves the use of neural networks and deep learning techniques, which are commonly associated with sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of real-world graphs, which could fall under sub-categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
